heaviest_rainfall.status: Today ranked 7th for the heaviest total rainfall during a storm, dropping a total of 23.86mm of rain over the storm duration of 31.0 hours with a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.6mm per hour during the storm today (ranking 2nd from our records) and resulted in 6.1mm of total rain in 2.6 hours.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 7th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 31.0 hours.  23.86mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  The lengthiest precipitation event recorded spanned 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025, it was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 24.6mm per hour and a total rainfall of 47.89mm.
